ed the amount determined in accordance with the following table:” and table of amounts for taxable years 1998 to 2001 and thereafter."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2005—Subsec. (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/135"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–135","children":[],"tail":" substituted “the Taxpayer Relief Act of 1997” for “this Act”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (b)(2)(C)(i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/357"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–357","children":[],"tail":" inserted “199,” before “222”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/311/s207/20"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–311, § 207(20)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “(determined without regard to subsections (b)(1), (b)(2), and (d)(1)(B) thereof)” after “section 152”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/311/s408/b/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–311, § 408(b)(5)","children":[],"tail":", amended directory language of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/16/s412/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–16, § 412(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":". See 2001 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2001—Subsec. (b)(2)(B)(i), (ii). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/16/s412/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–16, § 412(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", amended cls. (i) and (ii) generally. Prior to amendment, cls. (i) and (ii) read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(i) the excess of—","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(I) the taxpayer’s modified adjusted gross income for such taxable year, over","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(II) $40,000 ($60,000 in the case of a joint return), bears to","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(ii) $15,000.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(2)(C)(i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/16/s431/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–16, § 431(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “222,” before “911”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/16/s412/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–16, § 412(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (e) as (d), and struck out heading and text of former subsec. (d). Text read as follows: “A deduction shall be allowed under this section only with respect to interest paid on any qualified education loan during the first 60 months (whether or not consecutive) in which interest payments are required. For purposes of this paragraph, any loan and all refinancings of such loan shall be treated as 1 loan. Such 60 months shall be determined in the manner prescribed by the Secretary in the case of multiple loans which are refinanced by, or serviced as, a single loan and in the case of loans incurred before the date of the enactment of this section.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/16/s412/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–16, § 412(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (f) as (e). Former subsec. (e) redesignated (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/16/s402/b/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–16, § 402(b)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “529,” after “135,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/16/s412/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–16, § 412(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (g) as (f). Former subsec. (f) redesignated (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/16/s412/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–16, § 412(